  <prompt>
    Wire the Playbook Library modal into one ad-hoc launcher surface — the third and final FR-18
    consumer surface. The audit (task 093) identified the recommended ad-hoc launcher candidate
    (likely a LegalWorkspace ad-hoc panel, the Workspace pane menu in SpaarkeAi, or a sibling
    invocation surface). Add a "Browse Playbooks" affordance at the recommended mount point.
    Modal opens, lists every playbook with consumer mapping, clicking a playbook invokes it
    through proper Path A.5 routing. Reuse the shared PlaybookLibraryShell + mirror tasks 094/095
    Dialog wrapper pattern. This task closes FR-18's ≥3-consumer-surface acceptance criterion.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React / Fluent UI v9 developer familiar with the relevant ad-hoc launcher surface
    (per task 093 audit recommendation) — LegalWorkspace, SpaarkeAi Workspace pane menu,
    or similar. Reuse over invention.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The audit-recommended ad-hoc launcher now has a "Browse Playbooks" affordance such that:
    1. Affordance mounted at the location task 093 audit recommended for the ad-hoc launcher
       (e.g., LegalWorkspace ad-hoc panel toolbar, WorkspacePaneMenu overflow item, or sibling).
    2. Affordance triggers a modal Dialog wrapping PlaybookLibraryShell — mirrors tasks 094/095
       Dialog wrapper pattern for consistency across all 3 surfaces.
    3. Modal lists every playbook with consumer mapping per row.
    4. Clicking a playbook invokes it through Path A.5 routing — verified via BFF log inspection.
       Ad-hoc launcher context (current workspace, current entity) MAY be passed to invocation
       payload if the selected playbook is workspace-aware.
    5. Affordance follows ADR-021 (dark mode semantic tokens).
    6. Component test added in the appropriate __tests__ dir mirroring the surrounding pattern.
    7. Closes FR-18's "≥3 consumer surfaces wired" acceptance — verified by spec checklist update.
    8. Pattern parity with tasks 094 + 095 confirmed.
  </goal>

