  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: code-impl in Code Page (.tsx file modification, tags code-page + ui, ADR-013+021 applicable, FR-18 acceptance closing task) — quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md (FR-18) + plan.md (Wave 9) + task 093 audit doc.
      Re-read tasks 094 + 095 wiring (for pattern parity).
      Invoke the fluent-v9-component skill.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependencies">
      Confirm tasks 094 + 095 are complete + committed. Confirm audit doc's recommended ad-hoc launcher mount point.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read ad-hoc launcher host component">
      Open the file the audit recommended (e.g., LegalWorkspace ad-hoc panel OR WorkspacePaneMenu.tsx
      OR sibling). Identify the recommended mount point's exact insertion site.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Read tasks 094 + 095 wiring as pattern template">
      Open the files modified in tasks 094 + 095. Document the Dialog wrapper structure shared across both.
      This task mirrors that structure.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire affordance at recommended mount point">
      Add a "Browse Playbooks" Button at the recommended mount point in the ad-hoc launcher host.
      Wire onClick to open Dialog state (useState in the host).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wrap PlaybookLibraryShell in Dialog">
      Mirror tasks 094 + 095 Dialog wrapper exactly. Same DialogSurface / DialogBody / DialogContent /
      DialogActions structure. PlaybookLibraryShell as DialogContent body.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire playbook-selected callback to Path A.5">
      Mirror invocation pattern. If ad-hoc launcher context (workspace, entity) should be passed,
      include it in invocation payload. MUST flow through IInvokePlaybookAi (Path A.5).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="ADR-021 dark mode compliance">
      Semantic tokens. Dark mode toggle smoke.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Component test">
      Place test in the appropriate __tests__ dir of the host code page (mirror surrounding pattern).
      Test: affordance renders + click opens Dialog + onPlaybookSelected fires + Dialog closes.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Build + test">
      Run: npm run build:prod for the consuming app (per CLAUDE.md §12 — production build).
      Run: npm test for the new test.
      Goal: 0 errors; new test passes.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Manual smoke + FR-18 close-out verification">
      Deploy to spaarkedev1 dev. Manual smoke: open the ad-hoc launcher → click "Browse Playbooks" →
      modal opens → modal lists playbooks WITH consumer mapping → click → invocation flows through
      Path A.5 (verify via BFF logs).
      FR-18 close-out: confirm all 3 surfaces (spaarke-ai chat, briefing widget, this ad-hoc launcher)
      now host the affordance. Update spec.md Success Criterion #15 status (or document in
      notes/handoffs/) that ≥3 consumer surfaces are wired.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on new affordance + test. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-013 + ADR-021 + spec FR-18.
      Verify pattern parity with tasks 094 + 095 (cite the mirror in PR description).
      Verify FR-18 closure (≥3 surfaces) is documented.
      Fix any findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 096 status complete. Wave 9 now complete. Advance current-task.md to next pending
      task (likely Wave 4 task 041, which was blocked on Wave 9 task 091 completion). If TASK-INDEX
      tracks wave completion, mark Wave 9 ✅ in the status snapshot table.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Commit">
      Commit affordance + Dialog wrapper + test + FR-18 close-out note with conventional message.
      Example: feat(r7/wave9): wire Playbook Library modal into ad-hoc launcher (Wave 9 task 096, FR-18 closes ≥3 surfaces)
    </step>
  </steps>

